quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  16,10,"It is He Who sends down rain from the sky, from it you drink, and by it plants thrive on which you pasture your livestock"
  16,11,"He causes to grow therewith crops, olives, palm trees, grapevines and all kinds of fruits for you. Indeed, there is a sign in this for people who reflect"
  16,12,"And He has subjected for you the night and day, the sun and moon, and the stars are made subservient by His command. Indeed, there are signs in this for people of understanding"
  16,13,"And He has created for you various kinds of things on earth. Indeed, there are signs in this for people who take heed"
  16,14,"It is He Who has subjected the sea, so that you may eat from it tender meat and extract ornaments to wear. And you see the ships cleaving their way through its waves, so that you may seek His bounty and so that you may give thanks"
  16,15,"And He has placed into the earth firm mountains, so it does not tremor with you, and there are rivers and pathways so that you may find your way"
  16,16,and landmarks and the stars by which they find their way
  16,17,Is then He Who creates equal to one who cannot create? Will you not then take heed
  16,18,"If you try to count Allah’s favors, you will not be able to enumerate them. Indeed, Allah is All-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  16,19,Allah knows all that you conceal and all that you reveal
  16,20,"But those whom they invoke besides Allah do not create anything, rather, they themselves are created"
  16,21,"They are dead, not living; not even knowing when they will be resurrected"